    "client_msg_id": "06ab2e88-f84d-4236-ab4c-6ce401a5bbbf",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Thanks for sharing <@UCUSW7WVD>. I watched the whole little video from Felienne, and I _loved_ the ideas! There’s one part in <https://youtu.be/EdqT313rM40?t=1032|the video at 17m22s> where Felienne demonstrates an issue introduced by lack of syntax:\n```color is blue\nprint my favorite color is color```\nThis was such a cool example! Because, yes the syntax is too limited at this level, and the computer gets confused. But, that mistake is the learning process which then justifies why you have to use single quote chars to separate variables and text!",
